article.description: — Josip Vrankic scored 24 points on 10-for-13 shooting and Santa Clara withstood Pacific's late run in an 81-76 win in the second round of the West Coast Conference tournament on Friday night.
article.headline: Santa Clara advances in WCC eliminating Pacific 81-76
article.linkText: Santa Clara advances in WCC eliminating Pacific 81-76
article.story: LAS VEGAS -- — Josip Vrankic scored 24 points on 10-for-13 shooting and Santa Clara withstood Pacific's late run in an 81-76 win in the second round of the West Coast Conference tournament on Friday night. The seventh-seeded Broncos (12-7) advance to the third round to face No. 3 Pepperdine on Saturday. Guglielmo Caruso scored 14 points for Santa Clara and Keshawn Justice and Jalen Williams each scored 11. Daniss Jenkins scored 16 for No. 6-seed Pacific (9-9), Jeremiah Bailey and Pierre Cockrell II each scored 14, Jordan Bell 13 and Jahbril Price-Noel 10. ------ For more AP college basketball: https://apnews.com/hub/college-basketball and https://twitter.com/AP--Top25
